<subSubSection id="C30198A6FFFFFFC7FCABFA46FA8B73BB" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA4CB2DFFFFFFC7FCABFA46FC92709A" blockId="3.[813,1457,1498,1748]" box="[813,888,1498,1524]" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">NOTES</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA4CB2DFFFFFFC7FCABFA67FA8B73BB" blockId="3.[813,1457,1498,1748]" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">
In the original publication of this taxon, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8AB6DCFFFFFFC7FB71FA67FCB5735D" author="LECOMTE H." pageId="3" pageNumber="116" pagination="99 - 121" refId="ref13173" refString="LECOMTE H. 1928 a. - Ebenacees nouvelles de l'Indochine. Notulae Systematicae 4 (4): 99 - 121. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 6463259" type="journal article" year="1928">Lecomte (1928a: 105)</bibRefCitation>
only cited 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFFFFFC7FC66F986FBA9735C" box="[992,1091,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">Poilane 9</emphasis>
collected from “ 
<collectingCountry id="F30C8BBDFFFFFFC7FB7FF986FAA7735C" box="[1273,1357,1562,1588]" name="Vietnam" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">Annam</collectingCountry>
: Bangoi” as the original gathering. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8AB6DCFFFFFFC7FBC4F9A6FAFE733D" author="NGUYEN T. H." box="[1090,1300,1594,1621]" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" pagination="63 - 74" refId="ref13500" refString="NGUYEN T. H. 1996. - Fam. Ebenaceae Gurke, in AVERYANOV L. V., NGUYEN T. B., NGUYEN T. H., PHAN K. L., SEROV V. P. &amp; AKIMOVA G. A. (eds), Vascular Plants Synopsis of Vietnamese Flora. Russian Academy of Sciences, Saint Petersburg, Russia and National Center for Natural Sciences and Technology of Vietnam: 63 - 74." type="book chapter" year="1996">Nguyen (1996: 64)</bibRefCitation>
cited “ 
<emphasis id="B96F173FFFFFFFC7FAE5F9A6FCD1731C" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">Poilane 9</emphasis>
– P (holo)”, however, two sheets of this collection were located at P. Here we designate the specimen with barcode P00721429 as the 
<typeStatus id="54A0758FFFFFFFC7FC7FF905FBB473DB" box="[1017,1118,1689,1715]" pageId="3" pageNumber="116">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The sheet is the best preserved of the gathering and bears more extensive label data.
</paragraph>
